<p>
    The Mockingbird Society is an advocacy organization that works with young people and families to
    improve foster care and end youth homelessness. Our youth programs train young people who have been
    homeless or in foster care to be their own best advocates. By doing so, they change policies and
    perceptions that stand in the way of every child having a safe and stable home. Our family programs
    advocate for innovation in the way services such as foster care are delivered. Together, our solutions
    focus on improving the social service systems that ultimately serve thousands of children, youth and
    families each year in Washington and beyond.
</p>
